{"title_page": "Liu He (politician)", "text_new": "{{Chinese name|[[Liu]]}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n|name          = Liu He\n|native_name   = {{lang|zh-cn|{{nobold|\u5218\u9e64}}}}\n|birthname     = \n|image         = Liu He, May 16, 2018.jpg\n|imagesize     = 180px\n|caption       = Liu He in 2018\n|office        = [[Vice Premier of the People's Republic of China]]\n|premier       = [[Li Keqiang]]\n|alongside     = [[Han Zheng]], [[Sun Chunlan]], [[Hu Chunhua]]\n|term_start    = 19 March 2018\n|term_end      = \n|office1       = Director of the [[Central Financial and Economic Affairs Commission]] Office\n|term_start1   = 20 March 2013\n|term_end1     = \n|deputy1       = [[Chen Xiwen]]\n|1blankname1   = {{nowrap|General secretary}}\n|1namedata1    = [[Xi Jinping]]\n|predecessor1  = [[Zhu Zhixin (politician)|Zhu Zhixin]]\n|successor1    = \n|birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1952|1|25|df=y}}\n|birth_place= [[Beijing]]\n|death_date = <!--  {{Death date and age|}} or {{Death year and age| }} -->\n|death_place= \n|party      = [[Communist Party of China]]\n|spouse     = \n|children   = \n|relations  = \n|religion   = \n|education = [[Renmin University of China]]<br />[[Harvard University]]\n|footnotes  =\n}}\n\n'''Liu He''' ({{zh |s = \u5218\u9e64 |p = Li\u00fa H\u00e8 }}; born 25 January 1952) is a Chinese [[economist]] and politician, a current member of the [[Politburo of the Communist Party of China]] and the [[Vice Premier of the People's Republic of China]]. Liu is also the director of the Office serving the [[Central Financial and Economic Affairs Commission]] of the [[Communist Party of China]]; the latter headed by [[General Secretary of the Communist Party of China|Party General Secretary]] [[Xi Jinping]].<ref name=cv>{{cite news |title = Liu He |url = http://www.chinavitae.com/biography/Liu_He |accessdate=2015-04-08 |work=China Vitae }}</ref> He was named vice-premier on 19 March 2018 and is heading the [[Financial Stability and Development Committee]].<ref>{{cite web |url = https://www.ft.com/content/ceea03f4-2a85-11e8-9b4b-bc4b9f08f381 |title = China\u2019s Liu He to take broad economic role as vice-premier |date=19 March 2018 |website=Financia Times }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url = http://www.scmp.com/news/china/economy/article/2137860/liu-he-chinas-new-one-man-debt-bomb-disposal-unit |title = Liu He: China\u2019s new one-man debt bomb disposal unit |work=South China Morning Post |access-date=2018-03-19 |language=en }}</ref>\n\n==Liu He==\n===Early life===\nLiu was born in [[Beijing]]. He studied together with [[Xi Jinping]] at [[Beijing 101 Middle School]].\n\n===Education===\nLiu graduated from [[Renmin University]]-[[Beijing Union University]] with a degree in industrial economics. He later studied at [[Seton Hall University]] and received his [[Master of Public Administration|Masters of Public Administration]] at [[Harvard University]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.chinavitae.com/biography/Liu_He/bio|title=China Vitae : Biography of Liu He|last=Vitae|first=China|website=www.chinavitae.com|access-date=2018-03-19}}</ref>\n\n===Career===\nHe has published widely on macroeconomics, Chinese industrial and economic development policy, new economic theory and the [[information industry]].<ref name=\":0\" /> He worked successively for the [[National Development and Reform Commission|National Planning Commission]], the [[State Information Center of China|State Information Center]], and the [[Development Research Center of the State Council|Development Research Center]] of the [[State Council of the People's Republic of China|State Council]].<ref name=cv/>\n\nBeginning in 2013, Liu began advising General Secretary Xi Jinping on a series of economic initiatives, and was believed to be one of the primary architects of Chinese economic policy at the time. He was also a member of the Party [[18th Central Committee of the Communist Party of China|18th Central Committee]].<ref name=cv/>  Liu gave a keynote address to the 2018 [[World Economic Forum]] in Davos.<ref name=\"realstar\">{{cite news|last1=Bradsher|first1=Keith|title=At Davos, the Real Star May Have Been China, Not Trump|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/01/28/business/davos-trump-china.html|work=The New York Times|date=January 28, 2018}}</ref>\n\nAt the [[19th National Congress of the Communist Party of China|19th Party Congress]] in October 2017, Liu was promoted to the [[Politburo of the Communist Party of China|Politburo]]. In March 2018, Liu He was appointed as a [[Vice Premier of the People's Republic of China]].<ref>{{cite web |url = http://news.ifeng.com/a/20180319/56857742_0.shtml |title=\u56fd\u52a1\u9662\u526f\u603b\u7406\u3001\u56fd\u52a1\u59d4\u5458\u3001\u5404\u90e8\u90e8\u957f\u5b8c\u6574\u540d\u5355 |accessdate=2018-03-19 |date=2018-03-19 |agency=Xinhua }}</ref> In May 2018, Liu He, was also appointed top trade negotiator for the [[China\u2013United States trade war]]. In early October 2019, Liu He negotiated with his US counterparts on a preliminary trade deal.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2019-10-12/donald-trump-calls-truce-china-us-trade-war/11596668|title='You're very tough negotiators': Trump's truce in China-US trade war|date=2019-10-12|website=ABC News|language=en-AU|access-date=2019-10-27}}</ref>\n\n===Politics===\nHe has been described as \"one of the [[technocrat]]s that Xi Jinping trusts a great deal\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.newyorker.com/news/q-and-a/a-political-economist-on-how-china-sees-trumps-trade-war |title=Archived copy |access-date=2019-05-23 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20190523034716/https://www.newyorker.com/news/q-and-a/a-political-economist-on-how-china-sees-trumps-trade-war |archive-date=2019-05-23 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n===Personal life===\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{19th Politburo of the Communist Party of China}}\n{{13th State Council}}\n{{Vice Premiers of the People's Republic of China}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Liu, He}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:John F. Kennedy School of Government alumni]]\n[[Category:1952 births]]\n[[Category:People's Republic of China politicians from Beijing]]\n[[Category:Renmin University of China alumni]]\n[[Category:People's Republic of China economists]]\n[[Category:Members of the 18th Central Committee of the Communist Party of China]]\n[[Category:Members of the 19th Politburo of the Communist Party of China]]\n[[Category:Seton Hall University alumni]]\n[[Category:Economists from Beijing]]\n[[Category:Communist Party of China politicians from Beijing]]\n", "text_old": "{{Chinese name|[[Liu]]}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n|name          = Liu He\n|native_name   = {{lang|zh-cn|{{nobold|\u5218\u9e64}}}}\n|birthname     = \n|image         = Liu He, May 16, 2018.jpg\n|imagesize     = 180px\n|caption       = Liu He in 2018\n|office        = [[Vice Premier of the People's Republic of China]]\n|premier       = [[Li Keqiang]]\n|alongside     = [[Han Zheng]], [[Sun Chunlan]], [[Hu Chunhua]]\n|term_start    = 19 March 2018\n|term_end      = \n|office1       = Director of the [[Central Financial and Economic Affairs Commission]] Office\n|term_start1   = 20 March 2013\n|term_end1     = \n|deputy1       = [[Chen Xiwen]]\n|1blankname1   = {{nowrap|General secretary}}\n|1namedata1    = [[Xi Jinping]]\n|predecessor1  = [[Zhu Zhixin (politician)|Zhu Zhixin]]\n|successor1    = \n|birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1952|1|25|df=y}}\n|birth_place= [[Beijing]]\n|death_date = <!--  {{Death date and age|}} or {{Death year and age| }} -->\n|death_place= \n|party      = [[Communist Party of China]]\n|spouse     = \n|children   = \n|relations  = \n|religion   = \n|education = [[Renmin University of China]]<br />[[Harvard University]]\n|footnotes  =\n}}\n\n'''Liu He''' ({{zh |s = \u5218\u9e64 |p = Li\u00fa H\u00e8 }}; born 25 January 1952) is a Chinese [[economist]] and politician, a current member of the [[Politburo of the Communist Party of China]] and the [[Vice Premier of the People's Republic of China]]. Liu is also the director of the Office serving the [[Central Financial and Economic Affairs Commission]] of the [[Communist Party of China]]; the latter headed by [[General Secretary of the Communist Party of China|Party General Secretary]] [[Xi Jinping]].<ref name=cv>{{cite news |title = Liu He |url = http://www.chinavitae.com/biography/Liu_He |accessdate=2015-04-08 |work=China Vitae }}</ref> He was named vice-premier on 19 March 2018 and is heading the Financial Stability and Development Committee.<ref>{{cite web |url = https://www.ft.com/content/ceea03f4-2a85-11e8-9b4b-bc4b9f08f381 |title = China\u2019s Liu He to take broad economic role as vice-premier |date=19 March 2018 |website=Financia Times }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url = http://www.scmp.com/news/china/economy/article/2137860/liu-he-chinas-new-one-man-debt-bomb-disposal-unit |title = Liu He: China\u2019s new one-man debt bomb disposal unit |work=South China Morning Post |access-date=2018-03-19 |language=en }}</ref>\n\n==Liu He==\n===Early life===\nLiu was born in [[Beijing]]. He studied together with [[Xi Jinping]] at [[Beijing 101 Middle School]].\n\n===Education===\nLiu graduated from [[Renmin University]]-[[Beijing Union University]] with a degree in industrial economics. He later studied at [[Seton Hall University]] and received his [[Master of Public Administration|Masters of Public Administration]] at [[Harvard University]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.chinavitae.com/biography/Liu_He/bio|title=China Vitae : Biography of Liu He|last=Vitae|first=China|website=www.chinavitae.com|access-date=2018-03-19}}</ref>\n\n===Career===\nHe has published widely on macroeconomics, Chinese industrial and economic development policy, new economic theory and the [[information industry]].<ref name=\":0\" /> He worked successively for the [[National Development and Reform Commission|National Planning Commission]], the [[State Information Center of China|State Information Center]], and the [[Development Research Center of the State Council|Development Research Center]] of the [[State Council of the People's Republic of China|State Council]].<ref name=cv/>\n\nBeginning in 2013, Liu began advising General Secretary Xi Jinping on a series of economic initiatives, and was believed to be one of the primary architects of Chinese economic policy at the time. He was also a member of the Party [[18th Central Committee of the Communist Party of China|18th Central Committee]].<ref name=cv/>  Liu gave a keynote address to the 2018 [[World Economic Forum]] in Davos.<ref name=\"realstar\">{{cite news|last1=Bradsher|first1=Keith|title=At Davos, the Real Star May Have Been China, Not Trump|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/01/28/business/davos-trump-china.html|work=The New York Times|date=January 28, 2018}}</ref>\n\nAt the [[19th National Congress of the Communist Party of China|19th Party Congress]] in October 2017, Liu was promoted to the [[Politburo of the Communist Party of China|Politburo]]. In March 2018, Liu He was appointed as a [[Vice Premier of the People's Republic of China]].<ref>{{cite web |url = http://news.ifeng.com/a/20180319/56857742_0.shtml |title=\u56fd\u52a1\u9662\u526f\u603b\u7406\u3001\u56fd\u52a1\u59d4\u5458\u3001\u5404\u90e8\u90e8\u957f\u5b8c\u6574\u540d\u5355 |accessdate=2018-03-19 |date=2018-03-19 |agency=Xinhua }}</ref> In May 2018, Liu He, was also appointed top trade negotiator for the [[China\u2013United States trade war]]. In early October 2019, Liu He negotiated with his US counterparts on a preliminary trade deal.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2019-10-12/donald-trump-calls-truce-china-us-trade-war/11596668|title='You're very tough negotiators': Trump's truce in China-US trade war|date=2019-10-12|website=ABC News|language=en-AU|access-date=2019-10-27}}</ref>\n\n===Politics===\nHe has been described as \"one of the [[technocrat]]s that Xi Jinping trusts a great deal\".<ref>{{Cite web |