 and Roman Britain, Ancient Rome and Egypt, dinosaurs and fossils, ethnography\n|-\n| [[Hatton Gallery]] || [[File:Fineartbuildingnewcastle.jpg|125px]]  || [[Newcastle upon Tyne]] || [[Newcastle upon Tyne]]|| Art || Part of [[Newcastle University]]\n|-\n| [[Holy Jesus Hospital]] ||[[File:Front of Holy Jesus Hospital.jpg|125px]]  || [[Newcastle upon Tyne]] || [[Newcastle upon Tyne]]||  History || Operated by the [[National Trust for Places of Historic Interest or Natural Beauty|National Trust]], medieval building in use for 700 years, exhibits about its use as a 14th-century [[Augustinian]] [[friary]], 17th century [[almshouse]] and Victorian [[soup kitchen]]\n|-\n| [[Jarrow Hall]] || [[File:Northumbria 036.jpg|125px]]  || [[Jarrow]] || [[South Tyneside]]|| Multiple || Life and times of monk, scholar and author [[Venerable Bede]], includes artifacts from the adjacent medieval church, museum exhibits, Anglo-Saxon demonstration farm with heritage breeds of animals\n|-\n| [[Laing Art Gallery]] ||  || [[Newcastle upon Tyne]] || [[Newcastle upon Tyne]]|| Art || Collections include 18th and 18th century British oil paintings and sculpture, watercolours, ceramics, silver and glassware, 20th century art\n|-\n| [[Monkwearmouth Station Museum]] || [[File:Monkwearmouth Station Museum, Sunderland - geograph.org.uk - 121278.jpg|125px]] || [[Monkwearmouth]] || [[City of Sunderland]]|| Railway || Railway and transportation history and heritage\n|-\n| [[National Glass Centre]] || [[File:NGC 006 ngc front facia reduced.jpg|125px]] || [[Sunderland, Tyne and Wear|Sunderland]] || [[City of Sunderland]]|| Art || Historic and contemporary glass, history of glass-making\n|-\n| [[Newburn Hall Motor Museum]] ||  || [[Newburn]] || [[Newcastle upon Tyne]]|| Automotive || [https://archive.is/20100827011045/http://www.visitnortheastengland.com/site/what-to-see-and-do/attractions/newburn-hall-motor-museum-p25301 information]\n|-\n| [[North East Land, Sea and Air Museums]] ||[[File:North East Airc